claim.claim-text:
18. An apparatus capable of testing a displacement transducer having an extendable portion, the apparatus comprising: 
a slide capable of being reciprocated along an axis, the extendable portion being connectible to the slide so that, when the extendable portion is connected and the slide is reciprocated, the extendable portion is extended and retracted along a path that is substantially parallel to the axis; 
a measurement unit capable of measuring a displacement of the slide along the axis; 
a laser head capable of projecting a light beam and receiving a reflected light beam; 
an interferometer capable of allowing the light beam to propagate therethrough; and 
a first retroreflector fixed to the slide, the first retroreflector being capable of receiving the light beam and producing the reflected light beam, 
wherein at least a portion of the light beam and a portion of the reflected light beam propagate along paths that are substantially parallel to the axis.

38. A method capable of testing a displacement transducer, comprising: 
determining a plurality of electrical signal values outputted from the displacement transducer corresponding to a plurality of displacements of the displacement transducer; 
creating a statistical model based upon the plurality of electrical signal values and the plurality of displacements of the displacement transducer; 
determining a displacement error of the displacement transducer for each of the plurality of electrical signal values and the plurality of displacements of the displacement transducer based upon the statistical model; and 
determining which of the displacement errors exceeds a predetermined tolerance.

41. A method according to claim 38, wherein determining a plurality of electrical signal values outputted from the displacement transducer corresponding to a plurality of displacements of the displacement transducer comprises: 
extending an extendable portion of the displacement transducer to a plurality of predetermined displacements; 
measuring an extension dimension corresponding to each of the predetermined displacements; 
measuring an electrical signal outputted from the displacement transducer corresponding to each of the predetermined displacements.

43. A computer-readable program-storage device encoded with instructions that, when executed by a computer, performs a method capable of testing a displacement transducer, comprising: 
determining a plurality of electrical signal values outputted from the displacement transducer corresponding to a plurality of displacements of the displacement transducer; 
creating a statistical model based upon the plurality of electrical signal values and the plurality of displacements of the displacement transducer; 
determining a displacement error of the displacement transducer for each of the plurality of electrical signal values and the plurality of displacements of the displacement transducer based upon the statistical model; and 
determining which of the displacement errors exceeds a predetermined tolerance.

46. A computer-readable program-storage device encoded with instructions that, when executed by a computer, performs a method of testing a displacement transducer, according to claim 43, wherein determining a plurality of electrical signal values outputted from the displacement transducer corresponding to a plurality of displacements of the displacement transducer comprises: 
extending an extendable portion of the displacement transducer to a plurality of predetermined displacements; 
measuring an extension dimension corresponding to each of the predetermined displacements; 
measuring an electrical signal outputted from the displacement transducer corresponding to each of the predetermined displacements.

48. An apparatus capable of testing a displacement transducer having an extendable portion, the apparatus comprising: 
means for determining a plurality of electrical signal values outputted from the displacement transducer corresponding to a plurality of displacements of the displacement transducer; 
means for creating a statistical model based upon the plurality of electrical signal values and the plurality of displacements of the displacement transducer; 
means for determining a displacement error of the displacement transducer for each of the plurality of electrical signal values and the plurality of displacements of the displacement transducer based upon the statistical model; and 
means for determining which of the displacement errors exceeds a predetermined tolerance.
